{"key":"processedPost-17177568","value":{"id":17177568,"first":17171232,"last":17189425,"when":1352300023,"utime":"11/07/12 04:53 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>toneboy said:</b><br /><br />Regarding the lighting, is it true that lighting's impact is only crucial before pinning? If yes is there a time window in which lighting should be done in 12 hr increments.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />No.&nbsp; Light is a secondary pinning trigger, but it's effects are much more important <i>after pinning</i> when proper lighting can double or more the size and quality of your finished harvest.&nbsp; Remember, P cubensis will pin in total darkness.&nbsp; You have to be very careful around here with what you read, since new growers often repeat bad info they heard somewhere else.<br /><br />Simply mist a bit heavier if you're leaving for 2 days.&nbsp; I loathe the term \"set and forget\" because it implies laziness and this isn't a hobby for the lazy, but many growers have placed freshly dunked cakes in a shotgun terrarium and rarely if ever misted and had success.&nbsp; It's not ideal, but it also doesn't ruin your substrates to leave them for a day or two.<br />RR","title":"Re: Tips for battery powered automated misting and lighting"}}